  "texts": [
    "Prefetch Cache In our para-virtualization design, each request triggers message passing between the frontend and backend, incurring a fixed communication overhead regardless of data size.",
    "For small data transfers, this overhead can dominate execution time.",
    "A critical challenge is thus posed by frequent small-size data transfer operations, which led to repetitive frontend-backend communication, causing up to 53× overhead compared to native.",
    "These repetitive transfers typically result from the host application processing DPU data block by block in a loop.",
    "Consequently, these transfers generally occur within contiguous memory regions in the MRAM of the DPUs.Following this observation, we implement a prefetch mechanism within the frontend: 1 ○ At boot time, a prefetch cache is allocated within the frontend with the current implementation reserving 16 pages of cache per DPU."
  ],
